Sony has revealed its Xperia L1 smartphone, which boasts a stylish design and large display. The smartphone features a 5.5-inch HD display set within a seamless frame, and front and rear cameras. The Xperia L1 offers smooth performance thanks to its quad-core processor, 2GB of RAM, and 16GB of internal storage, said Sony. Software on the Xperia L1 includes Smart Cleaner, which automatically adjusts background tasks and memory usage to optimise performance, and Xperia Tips, which functions as a personal assistant and tunes the device’s functionality according to your preferences. South African pricing and release date information for the Sony Xperia L1 is not currently available.